The paper focuses on adversarial attacks in the context of autonomous driving, specifically on the visual perception pipeline which involves object detection and multiple object tracking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for generating adversarial examples, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves decision-making and safety considerations, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves security considerations, which suggests that it may belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves robotics and autonomous systems, which suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
